record_data.record_title: Revenue Requirement for Reactive Supply and Voltage Control
record_data.record_plain_text:
Title Page pursuant to 18 C.F.R. 35.10(a) Service Provider Meldahl, LLC Recipient of Service PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. Description of Service Provision of Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service from the Meldahl Hydroelectric Facility
MELDAHL, LLC SPECIFICATION OF COST-BASED REVENUE REQUIREMENT FOR THE PROVISION OF REACTIVE SUPPLY AND VOLTAGE CONTROL FROM GENERATION OR OTHER SOURCES SERVICE (MELDAHL FACILITY) Meldahl, LLC provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation or Other Sources Service ("Reactive Power Service") from the Meldahl Hydroelectric Facility ("Meldahl Facility") located on the Ohio River near Maysville, Kentucky that is interconnected to transmission facilities in the Duke Energy Ohio and Kentucky Zone operated by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM"). This Specification sets forth Meldahl, LLC's revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Power Service to PJM from the Meldahl Facility, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff. Meldahl, LLC's annual and monthly revenue requirements for this service are set forth below. ANNUAL AND MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENTS: Annual Revenue Requirement is $1,010,000.00 Monthly Revenue Requirement is $84,166.66 Effective: July 1, 2018 FERC Docket No. EL18-184-000
